.TH mlib_ImageConstMul_Inp 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_ImageConstMul_Inp \- multiply with a constant
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_ImageConstMul_Inp\fR(\fBmlib_image *\fR\fIsrcdst\fR, \fBconst mlib_d64 *\fR\fIc\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_ImageConstMul_Inp()\fR function multiplies each pixel in an image by a constant value on a pixel-by-pixel basis, in place.
.sp
.LP
It uses the following equation:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
srcdst[x][y][i] = c[i] * srcdst[x][y][i]
.fi
.in -2

.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIsrcdst\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Pointer to source and destination image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fB\fIc\fR\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt  
Constant by which each pixel is multiplied. \fBc[i]\fR contains the constant for channel \fBi\fR.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns \fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
